        "id": 2213829,
        "name": "Brandon Redman",
        "username": "Brandon_R",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/brandon_r/{size}/2555_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-07-05T20:25:31.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>1996 Woodward Canyon Chardonnay Celilo Vineyard (12.7%)</p>\n<p>After tasting a horrible, long-dead 1995 Columbia Valley Chard from the same produce, I wasn\u2019t optimistic.  However, this wine was fabulous.  The nose was shy, but showed some slight matchstick notes, with lemon peel.  On the palate, this was silky and bright, with lemon curd and faint orange blossom notes.</p>\n<p>These guys can make wine that really ages, and this vineyard in particular (tucked down near the Columbia River on the WA Side) really showed its merit for growing great Chardonnay.  I believe the vineyard was bought by the Corliss folks a few years back.  This, and Evergreen Vineyard, are my two favorite WA State sites for Chardonnay.</p>\n<p>(and, yet again, I apologize for the mis-oriented photos\u2026they were done upright on my phone, and appear normal after downloading on my laptop and phone\u2026I also can\u2019t find the explanation of where to correct this problem\u2026)<br>\n<img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/9/1/91ae8c570ea5dd5a17d16779ad49f6290e271ee9.jpeg\" alt=\"1996 Woodward Canyon Chardonnay cork sideways.jpg\" data-base62-sha1=\"kMLcsHMaG0dZ6ELkkOk14haxafD\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\"><br>\n<img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/5/0/503bb7168ef64c2f83d61a8135ac4d1e1760cceb.jpeg\" alt=\"1996 Woodward Canyon Chardonnay Celilo Vineyard sideways.jpg\" data-base62-sha1=\"brM8tZS1Mp4YYDNW75LmO1FeoFt\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\"></p>",
