      {
        "id": 2214049,
        "name": "Dale McClaran",
        "username": "Dale_McClaran",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dale_mcclaran/{size}/683_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-07-06T03:16:48.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hey Brandon, great post! While I too would have been suprised that a 21 year old chard from the ol\u2019 home state would show so well, the fact its Celilo fruit in some small way does temper the suprised factor. It\u2019s far and away the best Chardonany vineyard in the state IMHO. Did you try the Kerloo Chardonany from Celilo that was released last fall? Its pretty dang good, not sure it will go two decades, but no matter.</p>",
