        "username": "Drew_Goin",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/drew_goin/{size}/2421_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-07-06T12:02:54.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Chris Seiber\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Chris Seiber:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Brandon, I can\u2019t confirm this with certainty, but I\u2019ve read that if you modify the photo in any way first (angle, brightness, crop, whatever) then it appears on WB right side up.  It has seemed to work for me so far.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>+1</p>\n<p>On my cellphone, I go to my gallery app prior to attempting to attach the image. Then, I will click on the top-right screen corner to access the tool function. I usually select to \u201cRotate Right\u201d and then \u201cRotate Left\u201d to correct the picture to its original position.</p>\n<p>As Chris stated, any modification to an image prior to uploading it as an attachment to the forum will ensure that it displays correctly on your post.</p>",
