      {
        "id": 2214736,
        "name": "Brandon Redman",
        "username": "Brandon_R",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/brandon_r/{size}/2555_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-07-07T15:30:55.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I totally agree about Celilo Vineyard, though I haven\u2019t had Kerloo\u2019s.  I\u2019ll have to mosey on down to SoDo and see if they have any.  Try and seek out some Chardonnay from Evergreen Vineyard as well (in the Ancient Lake AVA).  I know Milbrandt does an inexpensive version, and Efeste does one as well (Lola Chardonnay).</p>\n<p>Thanks for the photo tips\u2026I\u2019ll try that.</p>",
